CatDescriptText: Marvin Slagenhaupt, assistant buyer, Eastwood and Willie Raab, steelworker, Penn Hills, were part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in the Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, April 9, 1960, pg. 29 with question "Do you believe the moral standards of our community have deteriorated since World War II?"  Mr. Slagenhaupt's answer reads: "Improved...But I think teen-agers still need more discipline."  Mr. Raab's answer reads: "I think they have improved."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Marvin Slagenhaupt wearing eyeglasses and tweed jacket, standing on sidewalk in front of intersection with street lights and buildings, Downtown; Portrait of Willie Raab wearing light colored hat and plaid shirt, standing on sidewalk in front of intersection with street lights and buildings, Downtown
